    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>finely chopped</strong> <strong>tomatoes</strong> with 100ml <span class=\"text-danger\">[180ml]</span> <strong>boiled</strong> <strong>water</strong>, a pinch of<strong> sugar</strong> and a generous pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong> and bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Cook for 2-3 min or until the turkey has cooked through and the sauce has thickened to a ragù-like consistency</p><p>Note: Please make sure you cook your turkey mince thoroughly (until piping hot!) as cooking equipment varies</p>",
